BFN 

  [Text] Amman--The Islamic Action Front, the Pan-Arab 
Action Front Party, and the Jordanian Arab Socialist Bath Party 
have issued the following statement: 
  A joint meeting was held at the Islamic Action Front Party's 
headquarters. It comprised representatives of these parties to 
discuss the tragic situation in fraternal Iraq under the unfair 
blockade imposed by the forces of tyranny and hegemony led by 
the United States. The conferees agreed on the following: 
  1. Calling on Jordanian parties to hold an urgent meeting in 
order to discuss ways to activate popular efforts, so they will 
play their role in lifting this unfair blockade; 
  2. Inviting a delegation from the Iraq Command of the Arab 
Socialist Ba'th Party to visit Jordan in order to hold 
consultations on the measures that can be taken to end this mean 
blockade; 
  3. Continuing the consultations and coordination among the 
three parties on various Jordanian, Arab, Islamic, and 
international issues. 

